metadata.name: Endurance
metadata.description:
"Through perseverance we shall overcome." - Sir Ernest Shackelton

I think about the story whenever I feel overwhelmed. The true story of the explorer Shackelton and the 27 men that sailed on the 'Endurance' for the Antarctic on an expedition in 1914. the goal was to cross the Antarctic. Unfortunately the ship got stuck and eventually sank November 21st, 1915 leaving all 28 men on the ice with only what they could salvage and drag over the ice.
All men were rescued in 1916. Everyone survived.

Artist: Annemarije de Boer
Camera: Canon EOS 5DS
Location: Venice Beach, California
Date: December 17th, 2022
ISO: 200
F-Stop: F/22
Exposure: 1/4s
Lens: 28mm
